Czech Pension Revamp May Lure Up to 12 Funds, Hospodarske Says

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-02-28T07:06:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/czech-pension-revamp-may-lure-up-to-12-funds-hospodarske-says.html
Czech Finance Minister Miroslav Kalousek expects 10 to 12 pension funds to manage private
savings for retirement after the government overhauls the
system,  Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing Kalousek.  Kalousek said the government may require the pension funds
to have at least 50,000 clients, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  